Description: Moulded pottery daily life shabti of Tjanefer, a priest of Amun, with painted detail: a black lappet-wig, a red face with black eyes, crossed arms and a triangular apron inscribed with a panel of black painted hieroglyphs, the feet are missing, the back is unmodelled.
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Somerset Lowry-Corry, 2nd Earl of Belmore
